As the stack trace you provided in the question indicates, the error is related to the fact that the Gson library, used internally by Jest for JSON processing, is not handling appropriately `null` values when processing some date values contained in your data.

The problem was reported in [this](https://github.com/google/gson/issues/1120) and especially [this other](https://github.com/google/gson/issues/1096) Github issues, and fixed in Gson [`2.8.2`](https://github.com/google/gson/compare/gson-parent-2.8.1...gson-parent-2.8.2).

The aforementioned issues indicate that everything should work properly with Gson 2.8.0, the version bounded with Jest, but please, in any case, due to the fact that AFAIK is not possible to define your own JSON (de)serializers or tweak the Gson existing ones when configuring Jest, try providing a version of Gson in which the problem is solved in your Maven or Gradle as a first level dependency, forcing your project to use it. For example:

```xml
&lt;dependency&gt;
    &lt;groupId&gt;com.google.code.gson&lt;/groupId&gt;
    &lt;artifactId&gt;gson&lt;/artifactId&gt;
    &lt;version&gt;2.8.2&lt;/version&gt;
&lt;/dependency&gt;
```

