 - it returns `true` if  `minValue &lt;= x &lt;= MaxValue` - i.e. within the range
 - it returns `false` if  `x &lt; minValue` **or** `x &gt; maxValue`  - i.e.
   out of range

Use with `if` condition as shown below:
