Stop fighting the dependency management that the Spring Boot starters do, also stop mixing jars from different versions of libraries (regardless of the library). 

- Spring Boot Starter Data JPA includes Hibernate and Spring ORM (remove those, as well as jdbc and tx)
- Use `spring-boot-starter-security` instead of manual declaring all security dependencies
- You already include the Spring Cloud parent, don&#39;t specify dependencies with versions
- Use `spring-boot-starter-websockets` instead of manual dependencies
- Use `spring-boot-starter-mail` instead of manual dependencies `javax.mail` etc
- Use the `spring-boot-starter-integration` dependency and remove the version from the ftp dependency
- Use `spring-boot-starter-aop` instead of directly aspectj (with old dependencies)
- Your spring cloud dependency is the wrong one you need 2021.0.3 to be compatible with Spring Boot 2.7

Which is, more or less, what was done in your working pom, but you decided to workaround that. 

